abstract: Aides to Ukraine’s leader, Volodymyr Zelensky, decided that military aid and support for peace talks outweighed the risks of appearing to take sides in American politics.
snippet: Aides to Ukraine’s leader, Volodymyr Zelensky, decided that military aid and support for peace talks outweighed the risks of appearing to take sides in American politics.
lead_paragraph: KIEV, Ukraine — It was early September, and Ukraine’s new president, Volodymyr Zelensky, faced an agonizing choice: whether to capitulate to President Trump’s demands to publicly announce  investigations against his political enemies or to refuse, and lose desperately needed military aid.

abstract: Rudy Giuliani wanted $500,000 to help a venture started by a man who would go on to help him in Ukraine. A Republican donor from Long Island put up the money.
snippet: Rudy Giuliani wanted $500,000 to help a venture started by a man who would go on to help him in Ukraine. A Republican donor from Long Island put up the money.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — It has been one of the enduring mysteries of the impeachment drama: Where did a cash-strapped Ukrainian-born American businessman get $500,000 to pay President Trump’s personal lawyer, Rudolph W. Giuliani?

abstract: The two officials are Tony Sayegh, a former Treasury aide, and Pam Bondi, a former Florida attorney general.
snippet: The two officials are Tony Sayegh, a former Treasury aide, and Pam Bondi, a former Florida attorney general.
lead_paragraph: Looking to strengthen its response to the impeachment inquiry initiated by House Democrats against President Trump, the White House has hired two officials to help manage its public efforts to defend the president, officials said on Wednesday.

abstract: With a Democratic governor in office, the party was in full control of Virginia state government for the first time in a generation.
snippet: With a Democratic governor in office, the party was in full control of Virginia state government for the first time in a generation.
lead_paragraph: Democrats completed Virginia’s historic partisan shift from red to blue on Tuesday, winning majorities in both chambers of the legislature and consolidating power across state government for the first time in a generation.

abstract: Joseph R. Biden Jr. escalated the war of words between the two leading Democratic candidates, painting Elizabeth Warren as unwilling to accept criticism of her plans.
snippet: Joseph R. Biden Jr. escalated the war of words between the two leading Democratic candidates, painting Elizabeth Warren as unwilling to accept criticism of her plans.
lead_paragraph: Joseph R. Biden Jr. unfurled sharply personal new lines of attack against Senator Elizabeth Warren on Tuesday, questioning her contributions to the Democratic Party and seeking to cast her as an elitist who believes people lack courage or wisdom unless they agree with her.

abstract: The party’s progressive and centrist flanks are each convinced that the other will lead to the president’s re-election.
snippet: The party’s progressive and centrist flanks are each convinced that the other will lead to the president’s re-election.
lead_paragraph: This article is the first in a two-part series for the Debatable newsletter about the 2020 presidential election. Thursday’s edition will cover Republican prospects next November. You can sign up here to receive Debatable on Tuesdays and Thursdays.
